  d['en']['ts.experts_p_4']='International Tax · Transfer Pricing';
  d['en']['ts.experts_p_5']='Partner, Tax Services';
  d['en']['ts.experts_h3_6']='Dyna Agustina';
  d['en']['ts.faq_p_1']='We serve mid-market to large enterprises, including publicly listed companies, multinational corporations, state-owned enterprises, and growing businesses with complex tax needs. Our approach scales to match your organization\'s complexity.';
  d['en']['ts.faq_span_2']='What size companies do your tax services cater to?';
  d['en']['ts.faq_p_3']='Transfer pricing is a core specialty. We prepare local files, master files, and country-by-country reports in compliance with Indonesian regulations and OECD guidelines. We also defend transfer pricing positions during audits.';
  d['en']['ts.faq_span_4']='Can you help with transfer pricing documentation for multinational operations?';
  d['en']['ts.faq_p_5']='Yes. We provide full representation in tax disputes, from administrative objections through the Tax Court and appeals process. Our team has extensive experience defending client positions and achieving favorable outcomes.';
  d['en']['ts.faq_span_6']='Does Chatura handle tax disputes with the Directorate General of Taxes?';
  d['en']['ts.faq_p_7']='Our tax team monitors regulatory developments continuously through direct engagement with tax authorities, professional networks, and ongoing training programs. We provide proactive briefings to clients before new regulations take effect.';
  d['en']['ts.faq_span_8']='How does Chatura stay current with evolving Indonesian tax regulations?';
  d['en']['ts.faq_h2_9']='Frequently Asked Questions';
  d['en']['ts.faq_span_10']='Questions &amp; Answers';
